<h1>About TravelApp</h1>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">About This Project</h2>
    <p>TravelApp is a Ruby on Rails application that lets users explore countries, cities, and tourist attractions around the world.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">Data Sources</h2>
    <p>The data for this project was generated using the <strong>Faker gem</strong>, which provides realistic fake data including country names, city names, attraction names, descriptions, and user reviews.</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">Database ERD</h2>
    <%= image_tag "ERD.png", class: "img-fluid", alt: "Database ERD" %>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="card mb-4">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h2 class="card-title">Database Structure</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Countries</strong> - name, region, population</li>
      <li><strong>Cities</strong> - name, belongs to a country</li>
      <li><strong>Attractions</strong> - name, description, belongs to a city</li>
      <li><strong>Reviews</strong> - rating, comment, belongs to an attraction</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The data follows a hierarchy: <strong>Country → City → Attraction → Review</strong></p>
  </div>
</div>